<subSubSection id="14DB6506A126FFC535ADFD355295FBD0" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="5C7E368DA126FFC535ADFD355295FBD0" blockId="15.[151,1436,687,1072]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="6EB5EA9FA126FFC535ADFD355353FCF0" bold="true" box="[199,513,759,784]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="9BC14D0EA126FFC5377BFD35521DFCF0" box="[529,847,759,784]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Lepidoblepharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heyerorum">
<emphasis id="6EB5EA9FA126FFC5377BFD35521DFCF0" box="[529,847,759,784]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Lepidoblepharis heyerorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Amazonia, widespread along the Amazon River, and the lower and middle portion of its main tributaries, occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="24D6761DA126FFC53102FCDE55FDFCD5" box="[1128,1199,796,821]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="24D6761DA126FFC531D7FCDE5435FCD5" box="[1213,1383,796,821]" name="French Guiana" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="24D6761DA126FFC535FDFC825199FCB7" box="[151,203,832,855]" name="Peru" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="C4FA2A08A126FFC535B3FCFD504EFCB8" box="[217,284,831,856]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1722,1744]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,195,1679]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,195,1701]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Distribution of examined material of Lepidoblepharis heyerorum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289018/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number id="EA0924AAA126FFC53466FC82504EFCB8" box="[268,284,832,856]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). It is most abundant, and with the majority of occurrences, in easternmost Amazonia (
<figureCitation id="C4FA2A08A126FFC53188FCFD5477FCB8" box="[1250,1317,831,856]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1722,1744]" captionTargetBox="[155,1436,195,1679]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,195,1701]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 9. Distribution of examined material of Lepidoblepharis heyerorum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289018/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number id="EA0924AAA126FFC5307FFC825477FCB8" box="[1301,1317,832,856]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="24D6761DA126FFC53032FCFD54CEFCB8" box="[1368,1436,831,856]" name="Brazil" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Brazil</collectingCountry>
it is known from the states of Amapá, Pará, and Amazonas. 
<taxonomicName id="9BC14D0EA126FFC5362FFCA6552FFC9D" box="[837,1149,868,893]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Lepidoblepharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heyerorum">
<emphasis id="6EB5EA9FA126FFC5362FFCA6552FFC9D" box="[837,1149,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Lepidoblepharis heyerorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits primary and secondary terra firme forests, creek valleys, and edges of swamps, where it is found among leaf litter, under fallen tree trunks, and among roots at base of trees and palms (
<bibRefCitation id="38504B7CA126FFC53146FC6E55F8FC24" author="Gasc" box="[1068,1194,940,964]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Gasc, J. P. (1981) Quelques nouvelles donnees sur la repartition et l'ecologie des sauriens en Guyane francaise. Revue d'Ecologie, La Terre et la Vie, 35, 273 - 325." type="journal article" year="1981">
Gasc 
<number id="EA0924AAA126FFC53105FC6E55F8FC24" box="[1135,1194,940,964]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1981.0">1981</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="38504B7CA126FFC531D2FC6E55A1FC25" author="Gasc" box="[1208,1267,940,965]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Gasc, J. P. (1986) Le peuplement herpeologique d' Astrocaryum paramaca (Arecacees), un palmier important dans la structure de la foret en Guyana francaise. Memoires du Museum d'histoire naturelle, Paris, Serie A, Zoologie, 132, 97 - 107." type="journal article" year="1986">
<number id="EA0924AAA126FFC531D2FC6E55A1FC25" box="[1208,1267,940,965]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; Hoogmoed &amp; Ávila Pires 
<number id="EA0924AAA126FFC53475FC125008FC08" box="[287,346,976,1000]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1989.0">1989</number>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="38504B7CA126FFC5340DFC0D5379FC08" author="Avila-Pires" box="[359,555,975,1000]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Avila-Pires, T. C. S. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">
Ávila-Pires 
<number id="EA0924AAA126FFC5349AFC0D5379FC08" box="[496,555,975,1000]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="38504B7CA126FFC53752FC0D5246FC08" author="Waldez" box="[568,788,975,1000]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Waldez, F., Menin, M. &amp; Vogt, R. C. (2013) Diversidade de anfibios e repteis Squamata na regiao do baixo rio Purus, Amazonia Central, Brasil. Biota Neotropica, 13, 300 - 316. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1676 - 06032013000100029" type="journal article" year="2013">
Waldez 
<emphasis id="6EB5EA9FA126FFC537FEFC13539DFC08" box="[660,719,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al.</emphasis>
<number id="EA0924AAA126FFC537BDFC125246FC08" box="[727,788,976,1000]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2013.0">2013</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="38504B7CA126FFC53642FC0D55CDFC08" author="Hoogmoed" box="[808,1183,975,1000]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Hoogmoed, M. S. &amp; Avila-Pires, T. C. S. (1991) Annotated checklist of the herpetofauna of Petit Saut, Sinnamary River, French Guiana. Zoologische Mededelingen, 65, 53 - 88." type="journal article" year="1991">
Hoogmoed &amp; Ávila-Pires (
<number id="EA0924AAA126FFC53137FC1255C5FC08" box="[1117,1175,976,1000]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="38504B7CA126FFC531B0FC0D51B3FBEC" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Avila-Pires, T. C. S., Hoogmoed, M. S. &amp; Rocha, W. A. (2010) Notes on the vertebrates of northern Para, Brazil: a forgotten part of the Guianan Region, I. Herpetofauna. Boletim do Museum Paraense Emilio Goeldi, Ciencias Naturais, 5, 13 - 112." type="journal article">
Ávila-Pires 
<emphasis id="6EB5EA9FA126FFC53008FC1354C7FC08" box="[1378,1429,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al</emphasis>
. (
<number id="EA0924AAA126FFC535F4FC36518BFBEC" box="[158,217,1012,1036]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
found it in moist areas in the forest. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="38504B7CA126FFC53787FC365572FBEC" box="[749,1056,1012,1037]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A., Gardner, T. A. &amp; Avila-Pires, T. C. S. (2008) Evaluating the effectiveness of herpetofaunal sampling techniques across a gradient of habitat change in a tropical forest landscape. Journal of Herpetology, 42, 733 - 749. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1670 / 07 - 097 R 3.1" type="journal article">
Ribeiro-Júnior 
<emphasis id="6EB5EA9FA126FFC536FDFC37529DFBED" box="[919,975,1012,1037]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number id="EA0924AAA126FFC536B7FC36554AFBEC" box="[989,1048,1012,1036]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
recorded a higher abundance of it in dry secondary forest, when compared with primary forest with creeks.
</paragraph>
